      "content": "That \"low-pH prison\" idea is wild lol. So basically it's like an invisible war happening in the jar. \n\nIs there any way to tell if that's what's happening just by looking at the bubbles or the texture? Like, are there specific signs that the bacteria have totally taken over versus the yeast being the main driver? I'm trying to figure out if I need to change my hydration or something to tilt the scales back.",
